data.title: Troup County, Georgia Government
data.meta_description: Troup County, Georgia Government | 451 followers on LinkedIn. #StartHere | Troup County is in West Georgia on the Alabama border. As a division of the State of Georgia, the County Government has an elected 5 member Board of Commissioners (4 districts and 1 at large) and an appointed County Manager. The County's primary functions are general administration, judicial, public safety, transportation and health and welfare.
